      <div resp="part:emfr" type="translation">
        <p n="1-3">
      			Second year of the victorious king, the king Nandivarman.
      		</p>
        <p n="3-11">
      			Vaṇṇakka Kaṭaiyaṉār, lord <supplied reason="explanation">
            <foreign>uṭaiya</foreign>
            <note><ptr target="bib:Mahalingam1988_01"/> simply translate as "of".</note>
          </supplied> of Tāḻaiyūr, fell liberating <supplied reason="explanation">
            <foreign>mīṭṭu</foreign>
          </supplied> cattle when Ūṇamiṟaiyār, a hunter <supplied reason="explanation">
            <foreign>vēṭṭuvar</foreign>
          </supplied> <supplied reason="subaudible">of</supplied> Iḷavenmaṟukkōṭṭu <supplied reason="subaudible">in</supplied> Vēṇāṭu, seized cattle <supplied reason="subaudible">at</supplied> Tāḷaiyūr.
      		</p>
